1934   // Iterate over IV uses (including transitive ones) looking for IV increments
1935   // of the form 'add nsw %iv, <const>'. For each increment and each use of
1936   // the increment calculate control-dependent range information basing on
1937   // dominating conditions inside of the loop (e.g. a range check inside of the
1938   // loop). Calculated ranges are stored in PostIncRangeInfos map.
1939   //
1940   // Control-dependent range information is later used to prove that a narrow
1941   // definition is not negative (see pushNarrowIVUsers). It's difficult to do
1942   // this on demand because when pushNarrowIVUsers needs this information some
1943   // of the dominating conditions might be already widened.
1944   if (UsePostIncrementRanges)
1945     calculatePostIncRanges(OrigPhi);
1946 
